{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 By default, the user can change the mode of a task. For example, the user could change the table shown here from Query to Modify, by pressing Ctrl+M or selecting Edit->Modify. Any mode changing option on the \i\f1 Options\i0\f0  menu would be available.\par
\par
If you want to restrict this behavior, set \cf2\i\f1 Task Properties->Options->Allow Options\cf1\i0\f0  to \cf2 No\cf1 . The user can then no longer change the mode for that task.\par
\par
In this example, you will see that no mode changing options are available on the Options menu.\par
